net.sourceforge.waters.model.module

Class ModuleProxyCloner

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sourceforge.waters.model.base.DefaultProxyVisitor
      • net.sourceforge.waters.model.module.DefaultModuleProxyVisitor
        • net.sourceforge.waters.model.module.ModuleProxyCloner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProxyCloner, ProxyVisitor, ModuleProxyVisitor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SourceInfoCloner

    public class ModuleProxyCloner
extends DefaultModuleProxyVisitor
implements ProxyCloner
    A tool to create deep copies of Module objects. Parameterised by a factory, this visitor can accept objects from one Proxy implementation and translate them to another.
    Author:
    Robi Malik

      • getClonedGraph

        public GraphProxy getClonedGraph(GraphProxy proxy,
                                 ModuleProxyFactory factory)
        Creates a clone of the given graph using two factories. This methods creates a clone of a graph's nodes and edges using the standard factory of this cloner, then creates a new graph using another factory given as an argument.
        Parameters:
        proxy - The graph to be duplicated.
        factory - The factory used to create the new graph.
        Returns:
        The cloned graph.
